node.text: I love this video.  This Airmen is exactly the type of Airmen you want to be friends with or have on your team.  His attitude and actions show no matter happens his future will be bright.  Why because he makes it bright.  I hope this energy spreads, a great Sunday vibe for the first day of August!  Big Salute to you A1C / Airman First Class,  Campise.

node.text: This is awesome!  Humboldt Bay, California crews, On June 19th, A 79 foot sailboat became disabled and the weather was getting bad.  Rescue swimmer and crew talk about a rescue this rescue.  First Rescue for the Rescue Swimmer.  Does the Coast Guard have a Talley of firsts like others in the USAF? First time you do something, you owe beer or that is how it used to be. #toml

node.title: Rescue Swimmer & Crew discuss a recent rescue!

node.text: Many ways to get to your  goals, this is a great example no matter what your goals are. Be realistic, I will never be a lead vocalist in a rock band no matter how hard I try.  Just not in the cards.  What's in the cards for you?  That's up to you for the most part and God given talent and drive.  God didn't want me to sing, that's all I can say🤣. This LT had a Business degree and wanted to be a pilot.  Air Force said no.  He joined as the enlisted ranks, and found another way.  Big Salute

node.text:
This is awesome & feel good video. A great Reenlistment Ceremony for Staff Sgt. Brenner, at Skydive Temple with Capt. Williams who provided Staff Sgt. Brenner the oath for his Army reenlistment, and accompanied him on skydive jump.

A huge thank you from First Army Division West was provided to local Veterans Scott Maschek, Federico Albacite, and Dena Donnell from Skydive Temple, and to Staff Sgt. Bermudezruelas and SSG Wiestling from 89th Military Police Brigade for  assisting for this the special occasion.

US Army photos and video footage by Master Sgt. Violet L. Dussault, Renention NCOIC, First Army Division West --thank you!

node.text: anding a CV-22 at a hospital needs to be validated.  We saw what happened when crews in the UK blew the landing surface apart at a local hospital.  Gryphon  Osx 21-1 was a recent training event to help validate this in Japan.  PJs (OR as PA called them Commando Medics) helped with this training event, by picking up the patient / process and package them.....for the hospital.  What are some of the things a PJ might do to package a patient prior to transload to the hospital?  #specialwarfareairmen

node.text: Ben Wilkinson, a professional big wave surfer and Patagonia ambassador from Oahu, Hawaii, tells about his experiences and provides his input regarding water and ocean safety. Rose and Cpl. Ryan H. Pulliam)

node.text: CCT boys with USMC....Non-combatant Evacuation Operations (NEO), are huge operations.  The CCT job is to run and control the airfield.  A Control Tower, has 3 positions with supervisors and safety.  Ground, Flight Data & Local Controller.  CCT does a bit more to replicate that and this includes, Landings/ Take-offs, Taxi, parking, helping set up and secure the airfield and passing information.  Here you can see the 24th MEU monitoring ATC with some CCT helping pass needed info to them directly. #specialwarfareairmen

node.text: Never Skip Leg day!  Upper body strength is always important especially when you don't use your legs.  Don't skip leg day at the gym or on the rope.  Easy to do and I myself have done it, not fun.

Awesome FLIR / Forward Looking InfraRed Radar.  Don't get stuck in the mud is a great metaphor.  Your thoughts, your actions or inactions etc.  In this case an Apache helicopter got stuck in the mind.  CH-47 heavy lift crews came to help.  I'm curious how much beer had to be paid for this.  Have a great Sunday and hope everyone in the North East, NY, CT, Mass areas stay safe and dry from Henri.

node.text: Basic medical skills are important as well as knowing how to evacuate a patient in the field. Air National Guard EOD getting some medevac training in.  EOD as well as other jobs require you know many things outside your specialty. Big Salute to the brave EOD folks kicking butt and making it safe everyday!

node.text: I have never SPIES over a big City!  These TACP made me jelly! node.text: So much going on these last few weeks mostly humanitarian stuff, evacuations and lets not forget about the Earthquake in Haiti.  PJs and CCT deployed on this humanitarian mission to help the sick and wounded and keep the flow of aid coming in to the airfield quickly and efficiently.  God Bless all the folks in Haiti and the those helping them recover. Stay positive and keep that energy flowing to others. #specialwarfareairmen

node.text: Happy Aviation Day to all maintainers, crews and pilots.  Everything we do and touch as a military person or civilian has been touched by these great folks.  Awesome Video to celebrate from the F-22 Airmen out of Florida!  Have a great day and keep those positive thoughts at the forefront of your brain pan.  #nationalaviationday

node.text: PJ's stand ready to jump into the ocean as part of a NATO led Search and Rescue Exercise.  The 106th Rescue Wing out of New York's National Guard brought their skills and Aircraft to the party.  The training was held in the middle of the Atlantic Ocean / The Azores which is a region of Portugal.  #specialwarfareairmen
